mmary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering ProxyObject simulation**\\n\\nI'm wondering if this approach might be okay in the context of ProxyObject simulation. But, I'm also not entirely sure. It seems like I could avoid issues with reflection by passing a null method to the handler, considering that the handler doesn't actually use it. It’s interesting to think about how my choices here could impact the overall functionality. There's definitely a lot to consider!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uDgkYOOHdQxmIHAripKgI8qd|fc_06f59b2502f31d040169f111142aac8193baa260044adadb49", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/ProxyFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void createsProxyWithConstructorArgumentsAndSerializesProxyDescriptor() throws Throwable {\n        ProxyFactory factory = new StaticProxyFactory();\n\n        GreetingService proxy = (GreetingService) factory.create(\n                new Class[] {String.class},\n                new Object[] {\"original\"},\n                new GreetingHandler());\n\n        assertThat(ProxyFactory.isProxyClass(proxy.getClass())).isTrue();\n        assertThat(proxy.prefix()).isEqualTo(\"original\");\n        assertThat(proxy.greet(\"Javassist\")).isEqualTo(\"handled:Javassist\");\n\n        byte[] serialized = serialize(proxy);\n\n        assertThat(serialized).isNotEmpty();\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void createsProxyWithConstructorArgumentsAndSerializesProxyDescriptor() throws Throwable {\n        ProxyFactory factory = new StaticProxyFactory();\n\n        GreetingService proxy = (GreetingService) factory.create(\n                new Class[] {String.class},\n                new Object[] {\"original\"},\n                new GreetingHandler());\n\n        assertThat(ProxyFactory.isProxyClass(proxy.getClass())).isTrue();\n        assertThat(proxy.prefix()).isEqualTo(\"original\");\n        assertThat(proxy.greet(\"Javassist\")).isEqualTo(\"handled:Javassist\");\n\n        byte[] serialized = serialize(proxy);\n\n        assertThat(serialized).isNotEmpty();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void generatedProxyClassReceivesStaticFactoryFields() throws Throwable {\n        ProxyFactory factory = new ProxyFactory();\n        factory.setUseCache(false);\n        factory.setUseWriteReplace(false);\n        factory.setSuperclass(GreetingService.class);\n        factory.setFilter(method -> method.getName().equals(\"greet\"));\n        factory.setHandler(new GreetingHandler());\n\n        GreetingService proxy = (GreetingService) factory.create(\n                new Class[] {String.class},\n                new Object[] {\"generated\"});\n\n        assertThat(ProxyFactory.isProxyClass(proxy.getClass())).isTrue();\n        assertThat(proxy.prefix()).isEqualTo(\"generated\");\n        assertThat(proxy.greet(\"factory\")).isEqualTo(\"handled:factory\");\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "            try {\n                Method method = GreetingService.class.getMethod(\"greet\", String.class);\n                return (String) handler.invoke(this, method, null, new Object[] {name});\n            } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n", "newText": "            try {\n                return (String) handler.invoke(this, null, null, new Object[] {name});\n            } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1537, "output": 1685, "cacheRead": 66048, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 69270, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777406211705, "responseId": "resp_06f59b2502f31d040169f111045424819389823141d8637cdf"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_uDgkYOOHdQxmIHAripKgI8qd|fc_06f59b2502f31d040169f111142aac8193baa260044adadb49", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/javassist/jav